{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"producer": "Canva", "creator": "Canva", "creationdate": "2023-07-06T19:39:51+00:00", "author": "Erin Human", "keywords": "DAFYyrGwRvQ,BAEwAah4POg", "moddate": "2023-10-05T07:12:00-05:00", "title": "A Neurodiversity and Gentle Parenting Journey\u2026in Color", "source": "corpus\\A-Neurodiversity-and-Gentle-Parenting-Journey.-in-Color.final_.pdf", "total_pages": 134, "page": 125, "page_label": "126"}, "page_content": "ABOUT AWN\nAutistic Women & Nonbinary Network (AWN) is a 501(c)(3) tax\nexempt non-profit committed to disability justice, gender and racial\nequity, neurodiversity, and trans liberation with a focus on trans-\nformative and restorative justice in disability spaces. The mission \nof AWN is to provide community support, and resources for Autistic\nwomen, girls, transfeminine and transmasculine nonbinary people,\ntrans people of all genders, Two Spirit people, and all people of\nmarginalized genders or of no gender. AWN is committed to\nrecognizing and celebrating diversity and the many intersectional\nexperiences in our community. AWN recognizes and affirms all\npeople\u2019s gender identities and expressions, as well as choices about\ndisclosure, transition, and keeping your identity private. AWN\u2019s goal\nis to dispel stereotypes and misinformation which cause unnecessary\nfears surrounding autism. AWN is committed to sharing information\nwhich works to build acceptance and understanding of disability.", "type": "Document"}}